@startuml
!theme plain
title PromptFlow React Streaming Chatbot - Architecture Overview

left to right direction

rectangle "User Browser" as Browser {
    [React App] as React
    [Chatbot Component] as Chatbot
}

rectangle "Web Server" as Server {
    [ASP.NET Core API] as API
    [ChatController] as Controller
}

cloud "Azure Services" as Azure {
    [PromptFlow Service] as PromptFlow
    [Azure OpenAI] as OpenAI
}

' Data flow
Browser --> Server : "1. POST /api/Chat\n{chat_input, chat_history}"
Server --> Azure : "2. Forward request\nwith Bearer token"
Azure --> Server : "3. Stream AI response\n(Server-Sent Events)"
Server --> Browser : "4. Proxy stream\nto frontend"

' Components within rectangles
React --> Chatbot : contains
API --> Controller : routes to
PromptFlow --> OpenAI : uses

note top of Browser
  User interacts with React chatbot
  Displays streaming responses in real-time
end note

note top of Server
  Proxy server for authentication
  Handles CORS and streaming
end note

note top of Azure
  AI processing and response generation
  Returns streaming text responses
end note

@enduml